WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:03.186 --> 00:00:04.364
<i>MALE NARRATOR:
Previously on</i> Prison Break:

2
00:00:04.388 --> 00:00:05.815
I didn't kill that man. Michael.

3
00:00:05.839 --> 00:00:07.105
The evidence says you did.

4
00:00:07.174 --> 00:00:08.440
I was set up.

5
00:00:08.509 --> 00:00:10.242
(GUN FIRES)

6
00:00:10.294 --> 00:00:11.843
<i>OFFICER: Put down your weapon!</i>

7
00:00:11.912 --> 00:00:14.440
I find it incumbent that you
see the inside of a prison cell.

8
00:00:14.464 --> 00:00:16.715
I'm looking for someone. A
guy named Lincoln Burrows.

9
00:00:16.783 --> 00:00:18.562
<i>SUCRE: Man killed the
Vice President's brother.</i>

10
00:00:18.586 --> 00:00:21.231
Why you want to see Burrows so
bad anyhow? Because he's my brother.

11
00:00:21.255 --> 00:00:22.399
I'm getting you out of here.

12
00:00:22.423 --> 00:00:23.505
It's impossible.

13
00:00:23.573 --> 00:00:25.601
Not if you designed
the place. it isn't.

14
00:00:25.625 --> 00:00:26.769
You've seen the blueprints.

15
00:00:26.793 --> 00:00:27.993
Better than that.

16
00:00:28.061 --> 00:00:29.862
I've got them on me.

17
00:00:29.930 --> 00:00:31.291
You find out who's
trying to bury him.

18
00:00:31.315 --> 00:00:32.564
Nobody's trying to bury him.

19
00:00:32.632 --> 00:00:33.999
The evidence was cooked.

20
00:00:34.068 --> 00:00:35.528
There's a lawyer poking around.

21
00:00:35.552 --> 00:00:38.002
Anyone that's a
threat is expendable.

22
00:00:40.490 --> 00:00:42.318
I'm gonna kill that scum.
SCOFIELD: You won't.

23
00:00:42.342 --> 00:00:44.688
You kill him. you kill our
express ticket out of here.

24
00:00:44.712 --> 00:00:46.289
What are you doing
here? Where's Maricruz?

25
00:00:46.313 --> 00:00:47.446
She's with me now.

26
00:00:47.498 --> 00:00:49.314
Fish. I gotta be back in.

27
00:00:49.383 --> 00:00:50.932
Nick Savrinn with
Project Justice.

28
00:00:51.001 --> 00:00:52.817
My boss may not
think Lincoln's case

29
00:00:52.886 --> 00:00:54.852
is worth looking into. but I do.

30
00:00:55.572 --> 00:00:56.788
When do we get started?

31
00:00:56.856 --> 00:00:58.652
Getting through this
wall is just the beginning.

32
00:00:58.676 --> 00:01:00.119
<i>There's a whole
lot of real estate</i>

33
00:01:00.143 --> 00:01:02.177
<i>in between here
and the outside walls.</i>

34
00:01:02.262 --> 00:01:03.996
That is a transfer request.

35
00:01:04.064 --> 00:01:06.815
<i>Michael Scofield is getting
shipped out tomorrow.</i>

36
00:01:08.552 --> 00:01:10.251
(WHIRRING)

37
00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:18.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

38
00:01:39.816 --> 00:01:42.634
I assume this is about your
transfer request for Michael Scofield.

39
00:01:42.703 --> 00:01:45.103
More specifically.
why you denied it.

40
00:01:45.322 --> 00:01:46.755
Look. Mr. Kellerman.

41
00:01:46.824 --> 00:01:50.225
do I come into your house and
tell you where to put your furniture?

42
00:01:50.294 --> 00:01:52.594
We're just asking for a
professional courtesy.

43
00:01:52.663 --> 00:01:55.509
But you're asking for a federal
courtesy in a state penitentiary.

44
00:01:55.533 --> 00:01:57.515
Most people in your
position would be happy

45
00:01:57.584 --> 00:01:59.262
to have another body
taken off their hands.

46
00:01:59.286 --> 00:02:00.880
These men are my responsibility.

47
00:02:00.904 --> 00:02:02.732
From the minute they
walk through those walls

48
00:02:02.756 --> 00:02:04.934
to the time that they've
paid their debt to society.

49
00:02:04.958 --> 00:02:06.425
I'm responsible for them.

50
00:02:06.493 --> 00:02:08.120
Which means that
unless Mr. Scofield

51
00:02:08.144 --> 00:02:09.689
has done something
I don't know about.

52
00:02:09.713 --> 00:02:13.148
he is gonna stay here at
Fox River. under my watch.

53
00:02:13.217 --> 00:02:14.828
Mr. Pope. in our line of work.

54
00:02:14.852 --> 00:02:17.396
we've discovered that just about
everyone has done something

55
00:02:17.420 --> 00:02:19.540
that someone doesn't know about.

56
00:02:21.809 --> 00:02:24.526
What's this? Right now.
just a piece of history.

57
00:02:24.595 --> 00:02:26.422
Whether it becomes
a current event.

58
00:02:26.446 --> 00:02:27.979
now. that's up to you.

59
00:02:33.136 --> 00:02:36.021
My wife already
knows about Toledo.

60
00:02:36.089 --> 00:02:37.405
Does she. really?

61
00:02:44.464 --> 00:02:46.397
You're a smart man. Warden.

62
00:02:46.466 --> 00:02:48.678
I'm sure if you look hard
enough. you can find a reason

63
00:02:48.702 --> 00:02:50.969
why Michael Scofield's
presence is no longer required

64
00:02:51.038 --> 00:02:53.278
at this particular
correctional facility.

65
00:02:58.629 --> 00:03:00.178
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

66
00:03:06.637 --> 00:03:08.517
I need some more PVC here. boss.

67
00:03:21.769 --> 00:03:23.935
Boss? Sure thing. Burrows.

68
00:03:23.987 --> 00:03:26.572
But. hey. I'm gonna check
your trunk for splinters.

69
00:03:26.640 --> 00:03:27.850
I want every piece
accounted for.

70
00:03:27.874 --> 00:03:28.923
Sure.

71
00:03:30.144 --> 00:03:32.794
I got a ripped
fertilizer bag inside.

72
00:03:35.432 --> 00:03:36.664
Hey. you.

73
00:03:37.417 --> 00:03:38.650
You.

74
00:03:39.586 --> 00:03:41.019
Get in there and clean it up

75
00:03:41.088 --> 00:03:44.008
before this whole place
starts smelling like San Juan.

76
00:03:46.409 --> 00:03:47.675
(MUMBLES IN SPANISH)

77
00:03:47.744 --> 00:03:49.143
Okay. he's on his way.

78
00:03:49.212 --> 00:03:51.572
Do you mind telling me
what this is all about?

79
00:03:55.769 --> 00:03:57.929
These are the guys
we're breaking out with.

80
00:03:58.872 --> 00:04:00.722
I don't think so. Fish.

81
00:04:00.791 --> 00:04:02.623
That was not our agreement.

82
00:04:03.744 --> 00:04:06.828
I'm not gonna work
with this crazy rhino.

83
00:04:06.897 --> 00:04:08.057
Keep pushing it. John.

84
00:04:08.081 --> 00:04:10.548
Yeah. I keep pushing
it. you know. Huh?

85
00:04:10.617 --> 00:04:12.684
What's your deal. man?

86
00:04:12.753 --> 00:04:14.869
Touch my brother
again. I'll show you.

87
00:04:19.376 --> 00:04:22.226
Brother? Your brother?

88
00:04:23.881 --> 00:04:25.213
(LAUGHS)

89
00:04:26.333 --> 00:04:28.166
We've only got a few minutes.

90
00:04:28.234 --> 00:04:30.146
Are we gonna spend
them spitting on each other.

91
00:04:30.170 --> 00:04:32.053
or are we gonna
talk some business?

92
00:04:32.122 --> 00:04:35.290
The reason we're all here today
is we have a decision to make.

93
00:04:35.359 --> 00:04:36.742
ABRUZZI: Yeah? English.

94
00:04:36.810 --> 00:04:38.377
Fitz or Percy.

95
00:04:38.445 --> 00:04:41.429
If we're gonna pull this off. we
need to take one of them out.

96
00:04:43.466 --> 00:04:46.251
And you want us to
tell you which one?

97
00:04:46.320 --> 00:04:48.386
I just want you to
help me get to them.

98
00:04:48.438 --> 00:04:49.737
I'll take it from there.

99
00:04:49.823 --> 00:04:50.934
You're crazy. you know that?

100
00:04:50.958 --> 00:04:52.067
All I need is five minutes.

101
00:04:52.091 --> 00:04:53.937
Oh. you won't even
get five seconds.

102
00:04:53.961 --> 00:04:55.977
Thought you had
everything worked out. Fish.

103
00:04:56.046 --> 00:04:58.596
We're not breaking out of
a Jamba Juice. gentlemen.

104
00:04:58.665 --> 00:05:00.932
It's gonna take a little more
than digging a few holes.

105
00:05:01.001 --> 00:05:02.417
There are eyes. ears.

106
00:05:02.485 --> 00:05:05.069
dots that couldn't be
connected from the outside.

107
00:05:05.138 --> 00:05:06.972
And English. Fitz and Percy?

108
00:05:07.041 --> 00:05:08.740
One of those dots.

109
00:05:11.211 --> 00:05:15.596
And how exactly are you
supposed to pull this off?

110
00:05:15.665 --> 00:05:17.915
With a little help
from my friends.

111
00:05:19.336 --> 00:05:21.136
(CELL DOOR OPENS)

112
00:05:21.205 --> 00:05:22.604
(INMATES CHATTERING)

113
00:05:35.385 --> 00:05:38.403
Sucre. hold up. Scofield.
you got company.

114
00:05:48.531 --> 00:05:50.632
Why do I get the feeling
that there's more to you

115
00:05:50.701 --> 00:05:52.221
than meets the eye. Scofield?

116
00:05:54.971 --> 00:05:56.521
Anything you wanna tell me?

117
00:05:59.843 --> 00:06:01.343
Some other reason you're in here

118
00:06:01.428 --> 00:06:03.728
besides holding up a bank?

119
00:06:15.809 --> 00:06:17.609
You're being transferred.

120
00:06:17.678 --> 00:06:18.777
What?

121
00:06:18.829 --> 00:06:20.749
We're moving you
over to Statesville.

122
00:06:21.465 --> 00:06:22.665
You can't do that.

123
00:06:22.699 --> 00:06:24.716
Yes. I can. I'm the boss here.

124
00:06:24.785 --> 00:06:26.118
This is my house.

125
00:06:28.104 --> 00:06:30.305
Three weeks. What for?

126
00:06:30.374 --> 00:06:32.256
Lincoln Burrows.

127
00:06:32.325 --> 00:06:34.626
He's being executed
in three weeks.

128
00:06:34.694 --> 00:06:37.028
Well. I'm aware of
that. What's that to you?

129
00:06:37.731 --> 00:06:39.014
He's my brother.

130
00:06:41.318 --> 00:06:43.329
When I knew I was
being sent to prison.

131
00:06:43.353 --> 00:06:45.820
my attorney petitioned the DOC.

132
00:06:45.889 --> 00:06:47.271
So you could be near him.

133
00:06:47.340 --> 00:06:48.640
That's right.

134
00:06:51.478 --> 00:06:53.111
Don't take that away from me.

135
00:06:54.714 --> 00:06:55.997
Not until it's over.

136
00:06:57.734 --> 00:07:00.535
I'm not the one
behind the transfer.

137
00:07:00.604 --> 00:07:02.787
You're up against much
bigger fish than me.

138
00:07:05.976 --> 00:07:07.808
I'll arrange for you
to say goodbye.

139
00:07:08.945 --> 00:07:10.545
You ship out tomorrow.

140
00:07:59.796 --> 00:08:01.716
<i>(MAN CHATTERING ON LOUDSPEAKER)</i>

141
00:08:37.433 --> 00:08:38.978
I'm going into
the walls tonight.

142
00:08:39.002 --> 00:08:40.418
See if I can access the roof.

143
00:08:40.487 --> 00:08:42.807
You gonna tell me
about the transfer?

144
00:08:43.173 --> 00:08:44.639
I'm taking care of it.

145
00:08:44.707 --> 00:08:46.774
You're taking care of it?

146
00:08:46.843 --> 00:08:48.643
Sounds to me like
you're reaching.

147
00:08:49.246 --> 00:08:50.678
Maybe.

148
00:08:50.747 --> 00:08:51.947
A little.

149
00:08:51.982 --> 00:08:54.599
(SIGHS) A little.

150
00:08:54.668 --> 00:08:56.846
You know. I'd made my
peace with what was coming.

151
00:08:56.870 --> 00:08:58.470
Then you show up

152
00:08:58.538 --> 00:09:01.206
and give me the one thing a
man in my situation shouldn't have.

153
00:09:01.274 --> 00:09:03.874
Hope. And now that's
gonna be taken away.

154
00:09:03.943 --> 00:09:06.444
Don't do this. Linc.
I got three weeks.

155
00:09:06.513 --> 00:09:07.996
What do you want me to do?

156
00:09:08.465 --> 00:09:09.597
Hmm?

157
00:09:14.454 --> 00:09:15.774
YOUNG LINCOLN: Come on. Michael.

158
00:09:15.822 --> 00:09:17.422
What do you want me to do?

159
00:09:19.493 --> 00:09:21.209
Bring her back.

160
00:09:21.277 --> 00:09:23.478
You know I can't do that.

161
00:09:23.546 --> 00:09:27.365
But. look. there's
some stuff that I can do.

162
00:09:27.434 --> 00:09:30.718
It's not gonna be the same.
but we're gonna figure it out.

163
00:09:30.786 --> 00:09:32.170
And no matter what.

164
00:09:32.238 --> 00:09:33.855
it's still gonna be me and you.

165
00:09:35.859 --> 00:09:38.626
Okay. But what if
something happens to you?

166
00:09:40.397 --> 00:09:42.997
You just have a little faith.

167
00:09:51.024 --> 00:09:52.524
Just have a little faith.

168
00:09:57.096 --> 00:09:58.456
NICK: All right.
here's the deal.

169
00:09:58.481 --> 00:10:00.281
If we believe Lincoln.
this tape is a lie.

170
00:10:00.350 --> 00:10:01.449
It has to be.

171
00:10:01.518 --> 00:10:03.095
But you saw it. It's all there.

172
00:10:03.119 --> 00:10:06.119
Yeah. but maybe what we're
looking for is what's not there.

173
00:10:07.557 --> 00:10:09.774
Okay. Steadman.

174
00:10:09.843 --> 00:10:11.676
You see? What's he looking at?

175
00:10:11.745 --> 00:10:13.127
VERONICA: A car. a pedestrian.

176
00:10:13.196 --> 00:10:14.962
No. no. His eye
line is too high. right?

177
00:10:15.031 --> 00:10:16.809
It's like he's looking
right into the camera.

178
00:10:16.833 --> 00:10:18.350
He might as well
be saying "cheese."

179
00:10:20.687 --> 00:10:22.120
Now he just sits there.

180
00:10:22.188 --> 00:10:24.500
Like 10. 15 seconds.
as if he was maybe...

181
00:10:24.524 --> 00:10:26.357
Waiting for someone. Right.

182
00:10:28.195 --> 00:10:29.677
There. That's a 9 mm.

183
00:10:29.746 --> 00:10:31.812
Shouldn't there be some
kind of kick or something?

184
00:10:31.881 --> 00:10:33.081
Lincoln's pretty strong.

185
00:10:33.166 --> 00:10:35.133
Yeah. but strong
enough to bury a recoil?

186
00:10:35.902 --> 00:10:38.052
Now. you shoot someone.

187
00:10:38.121 --> 00:10:39.571
supposedly for revenge.

188
00:10:39.639 --> 00:10:40.855
do you take the time

189
00:10:40.924 --> 00:10:42.301
to go back in and
hit the glove box.

190
00:10:42.325 --> 00:10:43.903
or do you just get
the hell out of there?

191
00:10:43.927 --> 00:10:46.289
Feds said he was trying to
make it look like a robbery.

192
00:10:46.313 --> 00:10:47.411
No.

193
00:10:48.831 --> 00:10:50.048
Look.

194
00:10:50.100 --> 00:10:52.700
Look at Lincoln's angle
as he leaves the frame.

195
00:10:52.769 --> 00:10:54.168
Mmm.

196
00:10:54.237 --> 00:10:55.703
Walks away from the car.

197
00:10:56.973 --> 00:10:58.439
Now this guy.

198
00:10:58.508 --> 00:11:00.925
who conveniently hides
his face from the camera.

199
00:11:00.994 --> 00:11:02.660
he comes back in. Why?

200
00:11:02.729 --> 00:11:05.691
To explain the bloody pants they'd
already planted in his apartment.

201
00:11:05.715 --> 00:11:07.515
Nick. this is great. Yeah.

202
00:11:08.718 --> 00:11:09.896
Who should we go to?

203
00:11:09.920 --> 00:11:10.985
Nobody. Yet.

204
00:11:11.054 --> 00:11:12.654
I mean. to the
unbiased eye. we're just

205
00:11:12.722 --> 00:11:14.289
backing a horse
that died in the gate.

206
00:11:14.357 --> 00:11:15.840
A lot of what-ifs
and conjecture.

207
00:11:15.909 --> 00:11:18.743
You know. we don't have
anything. We need some evidence.

208
00:11:18.812 --> 00:11:21.195
Look. if... if Lincoln
didn't fire this gun.

209
00:11:21.264 --> 00:11:23.964
then somebody with some serious
skills went to work on this tape

210
00:11:24.033 --> 00:11:27.153
to prove that he did. Fine.
But how do we prove that?

211
00:11:28.338 --> 00:11:30.054
I know a guy.

212
00:11:30.123 --> 00:11:31.839
You know a guy?

213
00:11:31.908 --> 00:11:33.408
Yeah. I know a guy.

214
00:11:34.344 --> 00:11:35.610
Thanks.

215
00:11:36.713 --> 00:11:38.875
Seems we need to
have another powwow.

216
00:11:38.899 --> 00:11:40.948
There's been talk about
you packing your bags.

217
00:11:41.017 --> 00:11:42.750
Don't believe
everything you hear.

218
00:11:42.819 --> 00:11:44.151
I'm not going anywhere.

219
00:11:48.124 --> 00:11:51.259
You know. I have a really
hard time trusting you. Fish.

220
00:11:51.328 --> 00:11:54.428
The important thing is
that we stay on schedule.

221
00:11:54.497 --> 00:11:56.181
Yeah? English. Fitz or Percy?

222
00:11:56.249 --> 00:11:57.731
English. Fitz or Percy.

223
00:11:57.800 --> 00:12:00.279
You wanna know which one
I think we should take out?

224
00:12:00.303 --> 00:12:02.269
All due respect. I
don't need opinions.

225
00:12:02.905 --> 00:12:04.422
I need answers.

226
00:12:04.491 --> 00:12:06.185
Remember. the warden
leaves at 5:00 tonight.

227
00:12:06.209 --> 00:12:08.375
So by 5:05. we're
gonna need that key.

228
00:12:08.461 --> 00:12:11.479
And how is this key gonna
give you the answers?

229
00:12:11.548 --> 00:12:13.131
I'll worry about that.

230
00:12:13.199 --> 00:12:14.810
You worry about getting the key.

231
00:12:14.834 --> 00:12:17.068
Hey. this key

232
00:12:17.137 --> 00:12:18.703
better be worth it.

233
00:12:18.772 --> 00:12:19.954
Understand?

234
00:12:26.813 --> 00:12:29.848
Afternoon. Mr. Scofield.

235
00:12:29.916 --> 00:12:32.951
I need to know if there's any
way to block a transfer order.

236
00:12:33.019 --> 00:12:34.419
There's about 50 ways.

237
00:12:34.487 --> 00:12:36.420
All right. I'll take
the quickest.

238
00:12:37.139 --> 00:12:38.506
You file a motion

239
00:12:38.575 --> 00:12:41.409
for what they call an
interlocutory injunction.

240
00:12:41.478 --> 00:12:42.610
How long does that take?

241
00:12:42.679 --> 00:12:44.278
How fast can you write?

242
00:12:44.347 --> 00:12:48.500
A man can claim almost anything
violates his constitutional rights.

243
00:12:48.568 --> 00:12:50.513
There's. uh.
environmental issues.

244
00:12:50.537 --> 00:12:52.417
allergies. religious
requirements.

245
00:12:52.471 --> 00:12:54.200
Take your pick. What
if they don't buy it?

246
00:12:54.224 --> 00:12:57.019
Don't matter. Court's required
by law to hear your motion.

247
00:12:57.043 --> 00:12:59.394
Till they do. you
can't be transferred.

248
00:12:59.462 --> 00:13:00.923
Hell. they've been
trying to move

249
00:13:00.947 --> 00:13:03.898
my tired gray
behind for 10 years.

250
00:13:03.966 --> 00:13:06.517
God bless the
American legal system.

251
00:13:07.721 --> 00:13:10.438
Why do you want to
stay in here so badly?

252
00:13:10.507 --> 00:13:13.357
There's someone here I
can't bear to leave behind.

253
00:13:14.593 --> 00:13:17.428
I guess that means we
got something in common.

254
00:13:18.981 --> 00:13:21.543
The State's requiring a
physical for Lincoln Burrows.

255
00:13:21.567 --> 00:13:23.379
You heard the news.
didn't you? Thanks.

256
00:13:23.403 --> 00:13:24.469
No. what?

257
00:13:24.537 --> 00:13:25.714
They're brothers.

258
00:13:25.738 --> 00:13:27.571
Who? Burrows and Scofield.

259
00:13:28.725 --> 00:13:30.174
Michael Scofield?

260
00:13:30.243 --> 00:13:32.527
Heard it from one of the
CO's over in Gen Pop.

261
00:13:32.595 --> 00:13:34.106
He didn't say anything
to you about it?

262
00:13:34.130 --> 00:13:35.630
No.

263
00:13:35.698 --> 00:13:38.377
Well. it must be hard to be
here so close to your brother

264
00:13:38.401 --> 00:13:40.601
and not be able to do
anything to help him.

265
00:13:49.012 --> 00:13:51.179
What's this? A little
bathroom reading.

266
00:13:51.247 --> 00:13:52.446
Westmoreland again?

267
00:13:52.532 --> 00:13:54.598
Scofield. He's
blocking his transfer.

268
00:13:58.905 --> 00:14:00.622
Even if the motion is denied.

269
00:14:00.690 --> 00:14:02.930
it's gonna take 30
days to process.

270
00:14:02.959 --> 00:14:04.153
And that means...

271
00:14:04.177 --> 00:14:05.493
(WHISTLES)

272
00:14:05.561 --> 00:14:06.978
(CHUCKLING)

273
00:14:07.047 --> 00:14:08.646
All right. I'm going in.

274
00:14:08.715 --> 00:14:10.314
I'm gonna need your help.

275
00:14:10.383 --> 00:14:13.000
You mean in in? Now? I
thought you were waiting till...

276
00:14:13.069 --> 00:14:15.163
I need to make sure I know
how I'm getting up there.

277
00:14:15.187 --> 00:14:17.438
so when the time
comes... Yo. yo. yo.

278
00:14:17.506 --> 00:14:20.324
In case you hadn't
noticed. the lights are all on.

279
00:14:20.393 --> 00:14:22.209
You got a live
studio audience. Fish.

280
00:14:22.278 --> 00:14:23.758
How you gonna get around that?

281
00:14:24.980 --> 00:14:27.140
Don't we have
some laundry to do?

282
00:14:32.288 --> 00:14:34.539
Just to be clear.

283
00:14:34.607 --> 00:14:36.574
I ain't touching your drawers.

284
00:14:47.386 --> 00:14:48.547
Eyes straight ahead.

285
00:14:48.571 --> 00:14:49.754
GUARD: Let's go!

286
00:14:50.406 --> 00:14:51.623
Keep it moving.

287
00:14:51.675 --> 00:14:52.795
GUARD: Eyes to the front.

288
00:14:52.842 --> 00:14:54.525
Keep it moving. keep it moving.

289
00:14:54.594 --> 00:14:55.709
Him.

290
00:14:59.114 --> 00:15:00.448
(ALL CLAMORING)

291
00:15:10.043 --> 00:15:11.192
(GUN FIRES)

292
00:15:13.062 --> 00:15:14.062
(GRUNTS)

293
00:15:16.215 --> 00:15:17.381
Get up.

294
00:15:20.804 --> 00:15:22.019
Stay down. Clear.

295
00:15:23.573 --> 00:15:24.855
GUARD: March.

296
00:15:25.575 --> 00:15:26.807
Come on.

297
00:16:29.806 --> 00:16:32.490
Fish? I can't deal with this.

298
00:17:12.398 --> 00:17:13.664
Fish.

299
00:17:14.500 --> 00:17:15.683
Come on.

300
00:17:30.950 --> 00:17:33.918
Yo. Fish. Fish. you're
taking too long. bro.

301
00:18:01.681 --> 00:18:03.175
SUCRE: This ain't
gonna fly. man.

302
00:18:03.199 --> 00:18:05.149
The Ricans. we got
genetically higher

303
00:18:05.217 --> 00:18:06.629
blood pressure. you know that?

304
00:18:06.653 --> 00:18:09.153
My cousin. he died
from too much stress.

305
00:18:09.221 --> 00:18:11.755
I thought you said your cousin
was moving in on your girl.

306
00:18:11.824 --> 00:18:14.892
That's my other cousin. But
thanks for bringing that up. jackass.

307
00:18:14.961 --> 00:18:17.527
Look. the good news is

308
00:18:17.596 --> 00:18:19.764
I can get to the roof.

309
00:18:19.832 --> 00:18:21.032
So what happens now?

310
00:18:21.100 --> 00:18:22.416
Now.

311
00:18:22.484 --> 00:18:24.051
it's all about timing.

312
00:18:25.955 --> 00:18:27.121
(BEEPS)

313
00:18:43.856 --> 00:18:45.239
(INMATES CHATTERING)

314
00:18:58.938 --> 00:19:01.033
This is a top dollar job.
Do you know who did it?

315
00:19:01.057 --> 00:19:02.606
No. Do you?

316
00:19:02.675 --> 00:19:05.742
People who do this kind
of work are ghosts. man.

317
00:19:05.811 --> 00:19:08.623
The guy behind the guy behind
the guy. You know what I mean?

318
00:19:08.647 --> 00:19:10.592
You see anything?
Definitive cuts?

319
00:19:10.616 --> 00:19:12.944
Any place that proves the
tape might have been doctored?

320
00:19:12.968 --> 00:19:14.847
The thing's clean.
No footprints.

321
00:19:14.871 --> 00:19:17.333
I mean. usually you peel the
video back a couple of layers.

322
00:19:17.357 --> 00:19:18.622
anything bogus comes off.

323
00:19:18.691 --> 00:19:20.536
You know. now you
see it. and now you don't.

324
00:19:20.560 --> 00:19:23.010
But not this one. It's laced.

325
00:19:23.078 --> 00:19:24.345
Ingrained.

326
00:19:25.265 --> 00:19:26.546
<i>(GUN FIRES)</i>

327
00:19:26.615 --> 00:19:28.477
Whoa. whoa. whoa.
NICK: You see something?

328
00:19:28.501 --> 00:19:31.652
No. The problem with your
eyes is that they play tricks on you.

329
00:19:31.721 --> 00:19:34.387
But your ears... Ears don't lie.

330
00:19:34.456 --> 00:19:37.841
Look. Here's the audio
track from the tape.

331
00:19:37.910 --> 00:19:40.161
There. Sound pretty
true. right? Yeah.

332
00:19:40.229 --> 00:19:41.829
But noise is alive.

333
00:19:41.897 --> 00:19:44.198
See. it doesn't
just die like that.

334
00:19:44.267 --> 00:19:46.795
Stripped down. those
levels should be dancing.

335
00:19:46.819 --> 00:19:49.220
A room that size would give you

336
00:19:49.288 --> 00:19:51.589
a... a "blam. blam.
blam. blam." you know.

337
00:19:51.657 --> 00:19:54.386
Like one off each wall. a
split second after the other.

338
00:19:54.410 --> 00:19:57.578
On yours. the reverb's
bouncing at the same time.

339
00:19:57.647 --> 00:19:59.029
What does that mean?

340
00:19:59.098 --> 00:20:01.214
The sound of the gunshot.

341
00:20:01.283 --> 00:20:03.301
It wasn't recorded in that room.

342
00:20:07.290 --> 00:20:09.423
Would you testify to that?

343
00:20:09.492 --> 00:20:10.969
(STAMMERING) I don't know.

344
00:20:10.993 --> 00:20:12.504
I mean. the tape you
gave me is a dupe.

345
00:20:12.528 --> 00:20:14.789
You know. for all I know.
you guys tampered with it.

346
00:20:14.813 --> 00:20:17.013
Look. you want me
to testify in court.

347
00:20:17.082 --> 00:20:20.562
I'm gonna need to get
my hands on the original.

348
00:20:23.940 --> 00:20:25.140
POPE: How are those allergies?

349
00:20:25.207 --> 00:20:26.406
Excuse me?

350
00:20:26.475 --> 00:20:27.742
(DOOR CLOSES)

351
00:20:27.810 --> 00:20:30.177
In your motion. you
cited chronic. uh...

352
00:20:30.246 --> 00:20:32.346
Sinusitis. Hmm.

353
00:20:32.414 --> 00:20:33.959
It's not an allergy. actually.

354
00:20:33.983 --> 00:20:36.317
It's a bacterial infection. Hmm.

355
00:20:36.386 --> 00:20:38.664
The moist air from the
river along the east wall

356
00:20:38.688 --> 00:20:40.215
helps keep me. you know.

357
00:20:40.239 --> 00:20:41.338
(SNIFFS)

358
00:20:41.407 --> 00:20:42.873
clear.

359
00:20:42.942 --> 00:20:44.975
I'm impressed. Not
even a week in here

360
00:20:45.044 --> 00:20:47.094
and you're already
working it like an old con.

361
00:20:47.163 --> 00:20:49.057
Well. you've got one
up on me. Warden.

362
00:20:49.081 --> 00:20:51.026
You know why I needed
to file those motions.

363
00:20:51.050 --> 00:20:54.468
but I have no idea why
you needed to transfer me.

364
00:20:54.537 --> 00:20:56.364
Traffic control.
Scofield. that's all.

365
00:20:56.388 --> 00:20:58.255
Traffic control.

366
00:20:58.324 --> 00:20:59.790
Look. it's coming up on 5:00.

367
00:20:59.858 --> 00:21:01.119
What do you say
we call it a day?

368
00:21:01.143 --> 00:21:02.604
(GRUNTS) I don't
think I can do that. sir.

369
00:21:02.628 --> 00:21:03.727
Why not?

370
00:21:03.796 --> 00:21:05.256
If I let go of this
support right now.

371
00:21:05.280 --> 00:21:06.975
the whole thing is coming down.

372
00:21:06.999 --> 00:21:09.683
See. the Taj was
designed using axial force.

373
00:21:09.752 --> 00:21:13.236
A series of internal forces
along the longitudinal axis...

374
00:21:13.306 --> 00:21:15.222
Yeah. How much longer?

375
00:21:15.290 --> 00:21:17.571
Depends on how
long it takes to dry.

376
00:21:18.026 --> 00:21:19.377
If you need me to leave.

377
00:21:19.445 --> 00:21:21.445
I can show your
secretary how to hold it.

378
00:21:21.514 --> 00:21:22.841
All right. you can
stay till it dries.

379
00:21:22.865 --> 00:21:24.576
There'll be a guard
waiting outside the door.

380
00:21:24.600 --> 00:21:26.077
Just check in with
Becky when you're done

381
00:21:26.101 --> 00:21:28.330
and she'll have somebody
escort you back to your cell.

382
00:21:28.354 --> 00:21:30.421
All right. And. uh. Scofield...

383
00:21:33.242 --> 00:21:35.709
I wanna thank you
for showing up today.

384
00:21:35.778 --> 00:21:37.844
I would have
understood it if you didn't.

385
00:21:37.913 --> 00:21:39.213
We had a deal.

386
00:21:39.281 --> 00:21:40.431
Right.

387
00:21:40.500 --> 00:21:41.932
Still. thanks.

388
00:21:42.001 --> 00:21:43.633
My wife is gonna love it.

389
00:21:43.702 --> 00:21:44.952
You're welcome.

390
00:21:49.642 --> 00:21:50.791
(DOOR CLOSES)

391
00:21:56.415 --> 00:21:58.048
PATTERSON: See
you tomorrow. sir.

392
00:21:58.116 --> 00:21:59.466
BECKY: Good night. Warden.

393
00:22:02.905 --> 00:22:04.655
We just happen to be two people

394
00:22:04.724 --> 00:22:06.590
who happen to know each other

395
00:22:06.659 --> 00:22:08.925
and happen to show up
at the same movie theater

396
00:22:08.994 --> 00:22:11.495
at what happens
to be the same time.

397
00:22:11.564 --> 00:22:12.712
(BECKY CHUCKLING)

398
00:22:12.782 --> 00:22:14.862
PATTERSON: That's
it. BECKY: I don't know.

399
00:22:52.221 --> 00:22:54.099
You know. from this angle.

400
00:22:54.123 --> 00:22:56.923
you look just as good as
you did when we first met.

401
00:22:56.993 --> 00:22:58.258
How about from this one?

402
00:22:58.327 --> 00:22:59.527
Even better.

403
00:23:02.431 --> 00:23:04.047
Oh. Uh-uh.

404
00:23:04.116 --> 00:23:05.816
Those are for your guests.

405
00:23:05.885 --> 00:23:07.984
Guests? Your associates.

406
00:23:08.053 --> 00:23:10.654
They said you had a
meeting. They're in the den.

407
00:23:19.748 --> 00:23:20.998
Evening. Warden.

408
00:24:06.779 --> 00:24:08.512
<i>POPE: There's nothing I can do.</i>

409
00:24:08.581 --> 00:24:11.242
I'm legally obligated to file
every properly drafted motion

410
00:24:11.266 --> 00:24:13.445
with the court. so that a
hearing can be scheduled.

411
00:24:13.469 --> 00:24:14.852
And how long does that take?

412
00:24:14.904 --> 00:24:17.154
A month. maybe
two if there's a logjam.

413
00:24:17.222 --> 00:24:19.022
I'm sorry. but it's
out of my hands.

414
00:24:19.074 --> 00:24:21.686
Why do I get the feeling
you're not all that disappointed?

415
00:24:21.710 --> 00:24:23.661
May I ask you a
question. Warden?

416
00:24:25.014 --> 00:24:27.481
More of an observation. really.

417
00:24:27.550 --> 00:24:30.050
I was looking at the
morgue. uh. photos

418
00:24:30.119 --> 00:24:32.886
of that boy back in
Toledo. Will Clayton.

419
00:24:32.955 --> 00:24:36.023
And. my Lord. if he wasn't
the spitting image of his daddy.

420
00:24:38.727 --> 00:24:41.607
Apple fell real far from the
tree with that one. didn't it?

421
00:24:42.631 --> 00:24:43.897
It fell off the tree.

422
00:24:43.966 --> 00:24:45.649
Fell all over the pavement.

423
00:24:46.501 --> 00:24:48.752
You son of a bitch.

424
00:24:48.821 --> 00:24:51.188
Your wife gave you
a pass on the affair.

425
00:24:51.257 --> 00:24:52.951
But something tells
me that's pretty much

426
00:24:52.975 --> 00:24:54.853
all the forgiveness
she's got left in her bag.

427
00:24:54.877 --> 00:24:57.327
Especially when it comes
to an illegitimate child.

428
00:24:57.396 --> 00:24:59.677
What happened with young Will.

429
00:24:59.765 --> 00:25:01.015
Warden?

430
00:25:01.867 --> 00:25:03.133
Get out of my house.

431
00:25:03.201 --> 00:25:04.768
Lose Scofield's paperwork.

432
00:25:06.939 --> 00:25:08.884
You gentlemen
staying for dinner?

433
00:25:08.908 --> 00:25:10.824
Thanks. but I think
we're on our way.

434
00:25:10.892 --> 00:25:12.042
Judy.

435
00:25:12.110 --> 00:25:13.905
it was a real
pleasure. Thank you.

436
00:25:13.929 --> 00:25:16.846
And that just may have been
the best iced tea I've ever had.

437
00:25:16.915 --> 00:25:18.432
(CHUCKLES)

438
00:25:18.500 --> 00:25:21.351
Warden. better do everything
you can to hold on to this one.

439
00:25:22.255 --> 00:25:23.453
I will.

440
00:25:23.522 --> 00:25:24.738
Good.

441
00:25:28.928 --> 00:25:30.427
Is everything all right?

442
00:25:30.495 --> 00:25:32.996
Oh. yeah. Just fine. I. uh...

443
00:25:33.065 --> 00:25:35.882
I just have a little unfinished
work to take care of.

444
00:25:35.951 --> 00:25:37.484
I'll be right in.

445
00:25:37.552 --> 00:25:38.785
Okay.

446
00:25:47.363 --> 00:25:48.895
(WHIRRING)

447
00:26:10.268 --> 00:26:11.701
(BUZZING)

448
00:26:16.642 --> 00:26:17.941
He's all clear.

449
00:26:19.211 --> 00:26:20.510
Good evening. Lincoln.

450
00:26:21.012 --> 00:26:22.312
Doctor.

451
00:26:22.381 --> 00:26:25.582
I'm. uh. supposed to give
you a physical this evening.

452
00:26:25.651 --> 00:26:28.351
Let me apologize in advance
for the heavy dose of irony

453
00:26:28.420 --> 00:26:29.881
we're about to participate in.

454
00:26:29.905 --> 00:26:32.690
That's all right.
Just doing your job.

455
00:26:32.758 --> 00:26:34.274
Yeah. well.

456
00:26:34.343 --> 00:26:36.721
letting the State know that
you're healthy enough to execute

457
00:26:36.745 --> 00:26:39.105
is not why I went
to medical school.

458
00:26:40.049 --> 00:26:41.181
I apologize.

459
00:26:41.250 --> 00:26:42.416
That's okay.

460
00:26:46.538 --> 00:26:48.805
All right.

461
00:26:48.874 --> 00:26:52.209
I'm. uh. going to need a
family medical history from you.

462
00:26:52.278 --> 00:26:55.345
Any ailments or conditions
that are hereditary.

463
00:26:55.397 --> 00:26:56.647
Start with your mom.

464
00:26:56.715 --> 00:26:58.948
Uh. cancer. Liver.

465
00:26:59.017 --> 00:27:00.350
Okay. Father?

466
00:27:01.487 --> 00:27:03.086
Mmm. split when I was young.

467
00:27:04.623 --> 00:27:05.889
Siblings.

468
00:27:07.026 --> 00:27:08.375
Anyone besides Michael?

469
00:27:11.930 --> 00:27:14.197
Fox River's a
small town. Lincoln.

470
00:27:14.266 --> 00:27:17.567
People around here don't have a
whole lot to do besides time and talk.

471
00:27:19.822 --> 00:27:20.904
You close?

472
00:27:23.408 --> 00:27:24.591
<i>LINCOLN: We were.</i>

473
00:27:27.780 --> 00:27:29.062
How about now?

474
00:27:29.131 --> 00:27:30.214
Huh?

475
00:27:30.266 --> 00:27:31.431
How about now?

476
00:27:33.052 --> 00:27:35.068
(SIGHING)

477
00:27:35.154 --> 00:27:37.320
<i>He's been abandoned
his whole life.</i>

478
00:27:38.791 --> 00:27:40.791
<i>Dad. Mom.</i>

479
00:27:40.860 --> 00:27:42.660
<i>She died young.</i>

480
00:27:42.728 --> 00:27:43.894
<i>And now me.</i>

481
00:27:46.381 --> 00:27:48.348
Think that's why he's here?

482
00:27:48.417 --> 00:27:50.217
'Cause your...

483
00:27:50.285 --> 00:27:52.769
Your death would feel
like it's happening again?

484
00:27:54.390 --> 00:27:56.406
<i>I abandoned him a long time ago.</i>

485
00:27:56.475 --> 00:27:57.891
<i>That's why he's here.</i>

486
00:28:22.801 --> 00:28:24.017
(WATCH BEEPS)

487
00:28:24.085 --> 00:28:25.218
(BUZZING)

488
00:28:25.287 --> 00:28:26.553
GUARD: Gates closing!

489
00:28:29.775 --> 00:28:30.941
It's time.

490
00:28:31.577 --> 00:28:32.809
Time?

491
00:28:32.878 --> 00:28:34.878
Oh. God. here we go again.

492
00:28:34.947 --> 00:28:36.892
Count's in 15 minutes.
What are you doing?

493
00:28:36.916 --> 00:28:39.032
Trust me. the less
you know. the better.

494
00:28:39.101 --> 00:28:40.212
The less I know...

495
00:28:40.236 --> 00:28:41.635
Man. you got me in the dark.

496
00:28:41.703 --> 00:28:43.620
That's exactly
where you want to be.

497
00:28:50.129 --> 00:28:52.595
BEN: Don't normally
find you here at this hour.

498
00:28:54.066 --> 00:28:55.365
Are you

499
00:28:55.434 --> 00:28:58.085
seeking his
forgiveness or advice?

500
00:28:58.153 --> 00:28:59.703
(LAUGHS)

501
00:28:59.772 --> 00:29:02.012
I really don't know
anymore. Ben.

502
00:29:03.842 --> 00:29:05.609
All I know is my son Will

503
00:29:07.078 --> 00:29:09.613
was my responsibility.

504
00:29:09.681 --> 00:29:12.282
And if I'd stayed in his life.
I could have saved his life.

505
00:29:12.350 --> 00:29:14.485
His death was an
accident. Henry.

506
00:29:19.024 --> 00:29:20.457
He was a criminal

507
00:29:21.093 --> 00:29:22.325
and an addict.

508
00:29:23.829 --> 00:29:25.562
But he was only 18 years old.

509
00:29:25.631 --> 00:29:29.116
His mother made it clear
you couldn't be in his life

510
00:29:29.184 --> 00:29:30.834
if you weren't
going to be in hers.

511
00:29:30.886 --> 00:29:34.454
When you chose to stay
with Judy. you understood that.

512
00:29:34.523 --> 00:29:36.923
I not only understood
it. I was grateful for it.

513
00:29:38.460 --> 00:29:42.195
I... I told myself I... I was
respecting her wishes.

514
00:29:43.932 --> 00:29:47.867
I cursed her under my
breath. while every day

515
00:29:47.936 --> 00:29:50.687
I thanked God for allowing
me to wash my hands of her.

516
00:29:51.757 --> 00:29:52.923
of Toledo.

517
00:29:55.794 --> 00:29:57.060
all of it. I...

518
00:29:59.564 --> 00:30:01.164
So I ran home

519
00:30:02.334 --> 00:30:03.500
to Judy

520
00:30:05.104 --> 00:30:06.803
and I buried the secret.

521
00:30:09.274 --> 00:30:11.207
But I never got a chance

522
00:30:13.078 --> 00:30:15.411
to bury my... my son.

523
00:30:16.849 --> 00:30:18.248
(SOBBING)

524
00:30:28.460 --> 00:30:30.727
What kind of a
person does that. Ben?

525
00:30:31.730 --> 00:30:33.730
Sacrifices somebody else's life

526
00:30:33.799 --> 00:30:36.333
just to make their
own life easier.

527
00:30:40.039 --> 00:30:41.999
You can argue with me all night.

528
00:30:42.023 --> 00:30:44.452
Believe me. I haven't
got anything better to do.

529
00:30:44.476 --> 00:30:46.192
But it won't change the fact

530
00:30:46.261 --> 00:30:49.729
that I can't just hand out
original copies of evidence.

531
00:30:49.798 --> 00:30:51.393
If you could just take a look...

532
00:30:51.417 --> 00:30:53.878
I don't care if your FOIL was
signed by the Attorney General.

533
00:30:53.902 --> 00:30:55.185
I can't give it to you.

534
00:30:55.254 --> 00:30:56.914
What if we brought
somebody here to watch it?

535
00:30:56.938 --> 00:30:59.222
Your supervisor could
monitor them the entire time.

536
00:30:59.291 --> 00:31:01.908
He'd strip down. swear on a
stack of Bibles. whatever it takes.

537
00:31:01.977 --> 00:31:04.377
Wait. what did you say
the docket number was?

538
00:31:05.247 --> 00:31:08.131
It's. uh. 296-SPE.

539
00:31:08.200 --> 00:31:09.511
(WHISPERS) Oh.

540
00:31:09.535 --> 00:31:10.695
What's wrong?

541
00:31:10.736 --> 00:31:12.496
(SIGHS) Come with me.

542
00:31:17.893 --> 00:31:20.460
Last night a pipe
burst upstairs.

543
00:31:20.529 --> 00:31:21.778
flooded the place.

544
00:31:21.847 --> 00:31:23.707
Files from over a hundred cases.

545
00:31:23.731 --> 00:31:25.999
Pretty much lost all of
them. including yours.

546
00:31:27.302 --> 00:31:28.468
Just this room?

547
00:31:28.537 --> 00:31:30.087
Some kind of freak accident.

548
00:31:31.757 --> 00:31:32.990
(WATER DRIPPING)

549
00:31:37.996 --> 00:31:39.296
(BUZZING)

550
00:31:41.666 --> 00:31:42.933
(WHISTLE BLOWS)

551
00:31:43.001 --> 00:31:44.234
GUARD: Count them.

552
00:31:44.303 --> 00:31:45.719
BELLICK: Callahan. Knight.

553
00:31:47.639 --> 00:31:49.789
Malinowski. Pohlen.

554
00:32:27.028 --> 00:32:28.227
(WATCH BEEPS)

555
00:32:34.753 --> 00:32:36.302
Chance. Graziano.

556
00:32:38.040 --> 00:32:39.805
Scofield. Sucre.

557
00:32:47.933 --> 00:32:49.065
Scofield.

558
00:32:50.469 --> 00:32:51.969
get the hell out here.

559
00:33:01.746 --> 00:33:03.113
We got a runner!

560
00:33:09.170 --> 00:33:10.754
(ALARM BLARING)

561
00:33:17.429 --> 00:33:18.445
(DOGS BARKING)

562
00:33:18.513 --> 00:33:19.729
<i>GUARD: Lockdown!</i>

563
00:33:20.882 --> 00:33:22.132
<i>Lockdown!</i>

564
00:33:24.920 --> 00:33:26.502
(INMATES YELLING)

565
00:33:34.846 --> 00:33:37.797
All right. for the
last time. <i>pinata.</i>

566
00:33:37.866 --> 00:33:39.448
Where the hell is Scofield?

567
00:33:39.517 --> 00:33:42.185
He's gone. you're
gone. You hear me?

568
00:33:42.254 --> 00:33:43.770
<i>PATTERSON: Call it off. Captain.</i>

569
00:33:43.839 --> 00:33:45.338
<i>I got Scofield right here.</i>

570
00:33:45.406 --> 00:33:46.523
Where?

571
00:33:46.592 --> 00:33:47.924
<i>In the warden's office.</i>

572
00:33:49.110 --> 00:33:51.511
You looking at him?

573
00:33:51.580 --> 00:33:54.764
<i>Stop trying to nail the secretary
and check the damn office!</i>

574
00:34:02.591 --> 00:34:03.723
Captain.

575
00:34:04.326 --> 00:34:05.491
he's gone.

576
00:34:06.061 --> 00:34:07.610
(ALARM BLARING)

577
00:34:08.463 --> 00:34:09.879
(DOGS BARKING)

578
00:34:16.454 --> 00:34:18.221
(SIRENS WAILING)

579
00:35:06.021 --> 00:35:08.683
The man can't just
vanish. Deputy. I know. sir.

580
00:35:08.707 --> 00:35:10.134
He never checked
out with you? No.

581
00:35:10.158 --> 00:35:12.003
And the rear door? Still
locked. sir. I checked.

582
00:35:12.027 --> 00:35:13.626
How the hell did he...

583
00:35:14.913 --> 00:35:16.379
What's going on?

584
00:35:16.447 --> 00:35:19.165
You're in the Warden's office
after hours. I could kill you

585
00:35:19.234 --> 00:35:21.779
and the paperwork wouldn't
need much more than the date.

586
00:35:21.803 --> 00:35:23.323
Tell me. what were
you doing in here?

587
00:35:23.355 --> 00:35:25.275
All right. Deputy.
that's enough.

588
00:35:28.143 --> 00:35:29.442
The work wasn't dry.

589
00:35:29.511 --> 00:35:31.792
You said to stay until it was.

590
00:35:31.846 --> 00:35:33.757
You were in here the
whole time? Yes. sir.

591
00:35:33.781 --> 00:35:35.343
It's true. I never
saw him leave.

592
00:35:35.367 --> 00:35:37.150
I must not have seen
him behind the table.

593
00:35:37.219 --> 00:35:39.252
Warden. all due
respect. this is ridiculous.

594
00:35:39.320 --> 00:35:41.604
This prisoner was out of
his cell. He missed the count.

595
00:35:41.673 --> 00:35:43.590
POPE: I understand. Deputy.

596
00:35:43.675 --> 00:35:47.210
The thing is. Mr. Scofield
is not our problem anymore.

597
00:35:47.279 --> 00:35:49.139
It seems there was an
error in his paperwork.

598
00:35:49.163 --> 00:35:51.114
He's going to be
transferred after all.

599
00:35:51.183 --> 00:35:53.332
That's not possible.

600
00:35:53.401 --> 00:35:56.019
Escort the prisoner
back to his cell.

601
00:35:56.087 --> 00:35:58.471
Warden. all I need
is three weeks.

602
00:35:58.540 --> 00:36:00.524
Get off me! Come on now.

603
00:36:00.592 --> 00:36:03.342
Henry. please.
just a little time.

604
00:36:03.411 --> 00:36:05.011
Just give me the time.

605
00:36:08.233 --> 00:36:10.994
Any chance you wanna
write this off as a coincidence?

606
00:36:11.353 --> 00:36:12.652
Me neither.

607
00:36:12.721 --> 00:36:14.965
How could they have known
we were coming for the tape?

608
00:36:14.989 --> 00:36:16.734
Three hours ago.
we didn't even know.

609
00:36:16.758 --> 00:36:18.658
Well. we're pissing someone off.

610
00:36:18.727 --> 00:36:20.638
You say that like
it's a good thing.

611
00:36:20.662 --> 00:36:23.730
People start breaking the law.
you know you're getting warm.

612
00:36:27.052 --> 00:36:29.736
We still have our copy
of the tape. so maybe...

613
00:36:34.275 --> 00:36:35.875
Nick. Stay here.

614
00:36:53.728 --> 00:36:55.661
Whoever it was is gone.

615
00:36:55.730 --> 00:36:57.247
Does it look like
they got anything?

616
00:36:57.315 --> 00:36:58.498
No.

617
00:37:04.356 --> 00:37:06.990
Everything's exactly
the way I left it.

618
00:37:16.318 --> 00:37:17.717
What? What?

619
00:37:21.389 --> 00:37:22.638
What?

620
00:37:22.707 --> 00:37:24.635
The tape. It's
gone. Are you sure?

621
00:37:24.659 --> 00:37:26.487
How could they know?
Let's think this through.

622
00:37:26.511 --> 00:37:28.139
How could they know
exactly where to look?

623
00:37:28.163 --> 00:37:30.057
Wait. does anyone else
have a key to this place?

624
00:37:30.081 --> 00:37:31.642
No. Are you sure this
is where you put it?

625
00:37:31.666 --> 00:37:33.449
You were here. remember?

626
00:37:33.518 --> 00:37:34.850
I was talking to you.

627
00:37:34.920 --> 00:37:37.787
I walked toward the
cabinet. and I s-said...

628
00:37:39.991 --> 00:37:41.157
What?

629
00:37:43.128 --> 00:37:45.295
Veronica. are you okay?

630
00:37:51.053 --> 00:37:52.335
Veronica.

631
00:38:00.394 --> 00:38:01.461
(BUZZING)

632
00:38:01.530 --> 00:38:02.730
BELLICK: Open up!

633
00:38:04.766 --> 00:38:07.233
Breakfast. gentlemen.
Let's move it!

634
00:38:07.301 --> 00:38:09.463
Sucre. let's go.
Scofield. wait here.

635
00:38:09.487 --> 00:38:11.688
I'm sure your ride will
be along any minute now.

636
00:38:19.714 --> 00:38:21.147
This can't be it.

637
00:38:22.384 --> 00:38:24.683
It can't end like this.

638
00:38:24.753 --> 00:38:26.252
BELLICK: Let's move it!

639
00:38:27.172 --> 00:38:28.304
SCOFIELD: Fitz.

640
00:38:29.274 --> 00:38:30.306
What?

641
00:38:30.375 --> 00:38:31.924
We were gonna take Fitz out.

642
00:38:33.495 --> 00:38:34.994
It was as clear as day.

643
00:38:37.683 --> 00:38:40.278
And the cops. how long
did it take them to respond?

644
00:38:40.302 --> 00:38:41.917
You got all the timing down?

645
00:38:46.341 --> 00:38:47.890
Think we would have made it?

646
00:38:51.062 --> 00:38:52.979
Sucre. now.

647
00:38:59.337 --> 00:39:01.321
♪ (ORANGE SKY PLAYING)

648
00:39:39.210 --> 00:39:41.310
<i>♪ Well. I had a dream ♪</i>

649
00:39:43.398 --> 00:39:46.015
<i>♪ I stood beneath
an orange sky ♪</i>

650
00:39:54.609 --> 00:39:56.876
<i>♪ Yes. I had a dream ♪</i>

651
00:39:59.297 --> 00:40:01.965
<i>♪ I stood beneath
an orange sky ♪</i>

652
00:40:03.835 --> 00:40:06.436
Hey. fish-face. where you going?

653
00:40:06.504 --> 00:40:10.206
<i>♪ With my brother standing by ♪</i>

654
00:40:13.928 --> 00:40:17.680
<i>♪ With my brother standing by ♪</i>

655
00:40:19.201 --> 00:40:21.367
Call my wife. Tell
her to get the kids

656
00:40:21.435 --> 00:40:23.286
and get the hell
out of the country.

657
00:40:25.306 --> 00:40:28.107
<i>♪ I said Brother.
you know. you know ♪</i>

658
00:40:29.644 --> 00:40:32.445
<i>♪ It's a long road
we've been walking on ♪</i>

659
00:40:38.786 --> 00:40:40.002
Sorry.

660
00:40:40.071 --> 00:40:43.606
<i>♪ Brother you know
it is you know it is ♪</i>

661
00:40:43.675 --> 00:40:46.392
<i>♪ Such a long road
we've been walking on ♪</i>

662
00:41:01.959 --> 00:41:03.593
Don't forget to buckle up.

663
00:41:07.532 --> 00:41:09.749
POPE: What's this
prisoner doing out of his cell?

664
00:41:09.818 --> 00:41:12.301
GUARD: He's being transferred.

665
00:41:12.370 --> 00:41:14.748
No. no. no. no. There must
be some kind of a mistake.

666
00:41:14.772 --> 00:41:16.433
This man filed a
motion yesterday.

667
00:41:16.457 --> 00:41:19.225
He has a medical condition
which precludes transfer.

668
00:41:19.894 --> 00:41:21.277
Sinusitis. right?

669
00:41:22.163 --> 00:41:23.479
Sinusitis.

670
00:41:24.649 --> 00:41:26.393
Take the prisoner
back to his cell.

671
00:41:26.417 --> 00:41:29.218
But yank his rec time.
He missed count last night.

672
00:42:11.462 --> 00:42:12.996
Hey.

673
00:42:13.064 --> 00:42:15.414
you're home early.
Everything okay?

674
00:42:16.200 --> 00:42:18.467
Yeah. Yeah. it is.

675
00:42:20.304 --> 00:42:21.871
There's just. um...

676
00:42:26.695 --> 00:42:27.810
Judy.

677
00:42:33.084 --> 00:42:35.084
There's someone I
need to tell you about.

678
00:42:37.905 --> 00:42:39.221
(PHONE RINGING)

679
00:42:40.191 --> 00:42:41.391
WOMAN: Yes?

680
00:42:41.459 --> 00:42:43.237
<i>KELLERMAN: The
transfer did not go through.</i>

681
00:42:43.261 --> 00:42:45.295
That's disappointing.

682
00:42:45.363 --> 00:42:46.774
<i>We can re-file.
but the warden...</i>

683
00:42:46.798 --> 00:42:49.098
It's a waste of time.

684
00:42:49.167 --> 00:42:52.618
I think it's time we stopped
beating around the bush. gentlemen.

685
00:42:52.687 --> 00:42:55.121
and go after the damn bush!

686
00:42:56.107 --> 00:42:57.223
<i>Burrows.</i>

687
00:42:58.192 --> 00:43:00.059
<i>What do you want done?</i>

688
00:43:00.128 --> 00:43:03.462
<i>WOMAN: Take the only
thing Burrows has left. Time.</i>

689
00:43:03.531 --> 00:43:05.565
<i>After all. the chair
isn't the only way</i>

690
00:43:05.633 --> 00:43:07.713
<i>to take a man's life in prison.</i>

690
00:43:08.305 --> 00:44:08.616
Do you want subtitles for any video?
